      • hasNext

        boolean hasNext()
        Indicates whether the fetch operation has a next page or not. This method can return true if there is a max parameter set in the Fetch Options and backend can return more results than this value. It should return false if this result is the last page of the fetch result, backend doesn't have more results than the max value, or max value is not set at all.
        Returns:
        true if fetch result has a next page

      • getNext

        Retrieves the next page of the results.
        Parameters:
        callback - FetchCallback that handles success and error situations of the operation.
